The paper discusses the emerging paradigm of Human-Machine Inference Networks (HuMaINs) which combines the cognitive strengths of humans and machines. This involves the use of machine learning and signal processing techniques to optimize inference performance. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also discusses the design of the HuMaINs architecture and its application areas, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper also addresses security and privacy challenges, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
